I don't understand the idea that mustache is logicless.<p>Why is something that shows a message "only if person has a truthy value":<p><pre><code>  {{#person}}
    Hi {{name}}!
  {{/person}}

</code></pre>
different from an `if` (except it becomes a `for` depending on the value of the argument)?<p>As long as you use values consistently it is never the case that a single person object referred by a variable "person" transforms into a set of people.
